    detailEn:
      "Kojiki and Nihon shoki tell how Amaterasu hides in the Heavenly Rock Cave, dimming the world until gods’ rowdy rites lure her out, tying light to sovereign order. Separate literary Kiki artifice from shrine performances that re-stage the myth; neither is the sole original scene, both charter solar legitimacy. This précis stays documentary rather than novelistic and invites comparison with regional variants. This précis stays documentary rather than novelistic and invites comparison with regional variants.",
