      "Yuki-onna tales crystallize in Meiji kaidan and local oral lore about mountain travelers, pale women, vows, and winter death risk. Read them through print culture plus regional fear of passes, not one text as nationwide orthodox cult; oaths mediate life at cold thresholds. This précis stays documentary rather than novelistic and invites comparison with regional variants. This précis stays documentary rather than novelistic and invites comparison with regional variants. This précis stays documentary rather than novelistic and invites comparison with regional variants.",
