    detailEn:
      "Umibōzu yarns in early modern coastal kaidan show bald sea giants interrogating boatmen, voicing labor risk and stranger seas. Read them as maritime oral tech for managing panic at open water, not one flattened cartoon; speech rituals try to bargain with the unknown swell. This précis stays documentary rather than novelistic and invites comparison with regional variants. This précis stays documentary rather than novelistic and invites comparison with regional variants.",
