    detailEn:
      "Mountain tengu lore fuses Shugendō idioms with sword tutelage, long-nosed yamabushi, pride, and ascetic trials amid forest taboos and samurai culture. Read tengu as ambivalent teachers, not one-note villains; mountain bans and martial lineages stack atop each other in medieval charters of skill. This précis stays documentary rather than novelistic and invites comparison with regional variants. This précis stays documentary rather than novelistic and invites comparison with regional variants. This précis stays documentary rather than novelistic and invites comparison with regional variants.",
