    detailEn:
      "Mithraic cults in the Roman world meet in subterranean mithraea, grade initiates, and center tauroctony reliefs, borrowing Iranian names yet forming a syncretic Latin military religion distinct from Avestan liturgy. Evidence is iconographic, epigraphic, and partial; we lack full Mithraic scriptures. The Persian connection is real but not a straight pipeline, so the archive classifies the mysteries as an imperialized sibling of Iranian light-hero veneration. This précis resists novelistic padding.",
